  "text": "The Grafana dashboard JSON schema version migration pipeline is a comprehensive system for evolving dashboard JSON from version 0 to version 42, implemented across backend Go code and frontend TypeScript code.\n\n## Backend Migration Runner (Go)\n\nThe migration execution is driven by `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/migrate.go`, which provides the public entry point `Migrate(ctx, dashboard, targetVersion)`. This function initializes a singleton migrator and manages the complete migration process including:\n\n1. Frontend defaults application (from `frontend_defaults.go`)\n2. Panel default value normalization\n3. Sequential execution of versioned migrations (v2 through v42)\n4. Dashboard cleanup for persistence\n\nThe `migrator` struct uses `GetMigrations()` from `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/migrations.go` to build a map of version numbers to migration functions. This registry returns `map[int]SchemaVersionMigrationFunc` with entries for all versions from 2 to 42.\n\n## Migration Function Registry\n\nThe core registry is in `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/migrations.go` with the `GetMigrations` function. It returns a complete map of migration functions:\n\n```go\nfunc GetMigrations(dsInfoProvider DataSourceInfoProvider) map[int]SchemaVersionMigrationFunc\n```\n\nThis function maps integer schema versions to `SchemaVersionMigrationFunc` types (functions with signature `func(context.Context, map[string]interface{}) error`). Some migrations like V33 and V36 require a `DataSourceInfoProvider` parameter to access datasource information during migration.\n\n## Individual Migration Steps\n\nEach schema version has a dedicated file in `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/` implementing transformations:\n\n- **V2 (v2.go)**: Migrates legacy `services.filter` structure to `time` and `templating.list`\n- **V6-V29**: Various panel type conversions, field structure updates, and annotation/variable migrations\n- **V30**: Upgrades value mappings and tooltip options\n- **V33 (v33.go)**: Converts panel datasource references from string names to UID-based structured objects (requires DataSourceInfoProvider)\n- **V34**: CloudWatch query and annotation migrations\n- **V35-V42**: Axis visibility fixes, datasource reference consolidation, table cell options, transformer updates, and field visibility migrations\n\nKey datasource-related migrations (V33, V36) use utility functions from `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/datasource_utils.go`:\n- `MigrateDatasourceNameToRef()`: Converts string datasource references to structured objects\n- `GetDataSourceRef()`: Creates datasource reference objects with uid, type, and apiVersion\n- `GetDefaultDSInstanceSettings()`: Retrieves the default datasource from available options\n\nSupporting utilities in `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/migration_utils.go` provide type-safe accessors for map values:\n- `GetStringValue()`, `GetBoolValue()`, `GetIntValue()`, `GetFloatValue()`\n- Type conversion helpers for numeric values\n\n## Frontend DashboardMigrator (TypeScript)\n\nThe frontend migration is implemented in `public/app/features/dashboard/state/DashboardMigrator.ts` as the `DashboardMigrator` class with the core `updateSchema(old, targetSchemaVersion?)` method. The constant `DASHBOARD_SCHEMA_VERSION = 42` marks version 42 as the final version for the v1 dashboard API.\n\nThe `updateSchema()` method mirrors the backend migration logic by:\n\n1. Iterating through schema versions sequentially\n2. Applying version-specific transformations via a `panelUpgrades` array\n3. Handling both dashboard-level and panel-level migrations\n4. Supporting nested panels within collapsed rows\n\nKey frontend migrations include:\n- Versions 2-28: Legacy field structure migrations and variable updates\n- Version 30: Value mapping upgrades\n- Version 33: Panel-level datasource string-to-reference conversion\n- Version 36: Complete datasource reference consolidation for annotations, variables, and targets (mirrors backend V36)\n- Version 38: Table display mode to cell options migration\n- Version 39: TimeSeries table transformer options update\n- Versions 40-42: Refresh property normalization, timepicker cleanup, and field hide functionality\n\nThe frontend also imports helper functions:\n- `migrateDatasourceNameToRef()` from DashboardMigrator for datasource migration\n- `getPanelPluginToMigrateTo()` for automatic panel type migrations\n\n## Integration Points\n\nThe backend and frontend migration pipelines work in concert:\n- Backend migrations transform the JSON schema on the server\n- Frontend `DashboardModel` applies defaults and normalizations during construction\n- The `DashboardMigrator` runs frontend-specific migrations with early exit if schema version matches\n- Test suites (`DashboardMigratorToBackend.test.ts`) verify backend and frontend produce identical results\n\nThe constant version 42 marks the final schema version for the legacy v1 dashboard API, with guidance that new feature migrations should be implemented in panel plugin migration handlers rather than adding dashboard schema versions."
